+## 2026-06-21 (claude/hex-color-chart-branding-svusth) — branding: saved color-palette library + colors now carry to new projects [PUSHED]
+
+- **Why:** colors didn't actually follow to new projects — global `/api/user/brand` PATCH dropped them (only wrote the 4 agent fields) and pre-fill only seeded agent fields. Operator also wants a library of saved schemes you pick from per project.
+- **What:** `lib/brand/palette.ts` (+ test, 11 cases) — `BrandPalette` shape `{id,name,colors:[primary,accent,extra]}`, `normalizeHex`/`sanitizePalettes` (validates, dedupes by scheme, caps 24), `defaultScheme`. `BrandingBlock.tsx` — always-visible **Saved palettes** row: click a chip to apply a scheme to THIS project, "+ Save as new palette" snapshots the 3 slots into the account library, `×` deletes. `ProjectWorkspace.tsx` — pre-fill now seeds empty color slots from the account default scheme (palette[0] → primary/accent/legacy columns) + loads the library; global **Save** auto-adds the current scheme to the library and persists colors. `app/api/user/brand/route.ts` — GET returns sanitized `color_palettes`; PATCH persists `primary_color`/`accent_color`/`logo_url` + the library. **Past projects never rewritten** — project.branding stays authoritative; the account default only seeds NEW projects.
+- **DB:** `docs/sql/20260621_user_brand_color_palettes.sql` adds `user_brand_profiles.color_palettes jsonb DEFAULT '[]'` (idempotent). **NOT YET APPLIED** — no Supabase creds in this web container. Code degrades gracefully (GET retries w/o the column; PATCH isolates the palette write) so it ships safe pre-migration: colors still save, library no-ops until the column lands. **Operator: run the migration to enable the library.**
+- **Gates:** `tsc --noEmit` exit 0 · eslint exit 0 · `bun test` brand+palette+digest **52/0** (route 12, palette 11, apply/resolve/projects/digest 40 unchanged). No deps, no lockfile change.
+
 ## 2026-06-21 (claude/hex-color-chart-branding-svusth) — branding: hex input + color chart + 3 save slots [PUSHED]
 
 - **What:** `app/project/[id]/workspace/BrandingBlock.tsx` — added a "Brand colors" section to the Brand pill popover. Live preview swatch + a hex text input (loose-hex `normalizeHex`: accepts `abc`/`#ABC`/`001122` → `#rrggbb`) + native `<input type=color>` + a 20-swatch **color chart** grid you click to pick. Three **save slots** below — clicking "Save" drops the current draft color into a slot; clicking a filled slot loads it back into the picker; `×` clears it.
